Make Matsuhisa Salsa: Combine all the ingredients. Add the parsley just before use.
Make Maui Onion Salsa: Combine all ingredients.
Make Jalapeño Salsa: Combine all ingredients.
Assemble oysters: 1. Remove the oysters from their shells and rinse under cold water. Drain.
2. Arrange the oysters in their shells on a serving dish lined with crushed ice and top with a little of each salsa — i.e. four oysters per salsa.
3. Sprinkle the chives over the Maui Onion Salsa.
